title.rendered: Australia vs Bangladesh, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023: Fantasy Team, Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Playing XIs for Australia & Bangladesh

Australia: Alyssa Healy (wk), Beth Mooney, Meg Lanning (c), Ashleigh Gardner, Ellyse Perry, Grace Harris, Tahlia McGrath, Jess Jonassen, Alana King, Megan Schutt, Darcie Brown

Bangladesh: Shamima Sultana (wk), Murshida Khatun, Sobhana Mostary, Nigar Sultana (c), Shorna Akter, Ritu Moni, Lata Mondal, Nahida Akter, Marufa Akter, Salma Khatun, Jahanara Alam

Pitch Report for Australia vs Bangladesh, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023

Venue: St George’s Park, Gqeberha

No women’s T20I has been played at the venue. The following data is based on the last three matches of the recently concluded South Africa T20 League.

1st innings average score: 156

2nd innings average score: 118

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Slow wicket

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Also Read:

India vs West Indies, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023: Fantasy Tips

New Zealand vs England, 1st Test, 2023 Fantasy Tips

Pakistan vs Ireland, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023: Fantasy Cricket Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

In the only T20I between these teams, Alyssa Healy (83 off 53) and Beth Mooney (81* off 58) smashed the Bangladesh bowlers to pulp. Later, Megan Schutt (3 for 31) and Jess Jonassen (2 for 17) bowled well in tandem and reduced Bangladesh to 103 for 9.

Ashleigh Gardner’s recent stats are encouraging for fantasy players. In her last five matches, she has scored 146 runs at an average of 49 and taken 10 wickets.

Marufa Akter’s Best11 percentage in the last five games read 80. Above all, she has gone wicketless only once in the last 10 games, overall taking 17 wickets.

Nigar Sultana and Murshida Khatun are the only two Bangladeshi batters to average over 25 since 2022.

In the same period, Nahida Akter has been the pick of the bowlers. She has scalped 22 wickets in 15 games including the best figures of 5 for 12.

As has been the case throughout the World Cup, spinners are yet again likely to take centre stage. While we have already shed light on Jess, Ashleigh, and Nahida’s finger-spin, one cannot ignore the threat of Alana King’s leg-spin.
